%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-is-inflation-looking-consumer-price-index-june-data-2023-7%5C%22%3EJune%20CPI%20report%20revealed%20that%20inflation%20has%20dropped%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20its%20lowest%20level%20in%20more%20than%20two%20years%2C%20and%20that's%20great%20news%20for%20both%20the%20economy%20and%20the%20stock%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20consumer%20price%20index%20rose%20just%200.2%25%20in%20June%2C%20below%20economists'%20estimates%20for%20a%200.3%25%20gain%2C%20and%20rose%20just%203%25%20on%20a%20year-over-year%20basis%2C%20its%20lowest%20level%20since%20March%202021%20and%20below%20estimates%20of%20a%203.1%25%20gain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20positive%20inflation%20surprise%20was%20welcomed%20by%20investors%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Findex%2Fdow_jones%5C%22%3EDow%20Jones%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Findex%2Fnasdaq_100%5C%22%3ENasdaq%20100%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Findex%2Fs%26amp%3Bp_500%5C%22%3ES%26amp%3BP%20500%3C%2Fa%3E%20all%20surged%20about%201%25.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20a%20strong%20move%20higher%20was%20no%20surprise%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffsinsight.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFundstrat's%3C%2Fa%3E%20Tom%20Lee%2C%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fstock-market-outlook-cpi-inflation-drop-sp500-rally-this-week-2023-7%5C%22%3Eforecasted%20at%20the%20start%20of%20this%20week%20that%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20was%20poised%20for%20a%20100%20point%20rally%3C%2Fa%3E%20sparked%20by%20a%20better-than-expected%20inflation%20reading.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20Lee%20is%20arguing%20that%20a%20100%20point%20rally%20in%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20this%20week%20could%20be%20on%20the%20low%20end%2C%20with%20a%20potential%20rally%20driving%20a%20more%20than%20200%20point%20gain%20in%20the%20index.%20Such%20a%20gain%20would%20send%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20to%20new%2052-week%20highs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOf%20the%20last%208%20CPI%20reports%2C%20markets%20had%20a%20positive%20reaction%206%20of%208%20times.%20The%20two%20'surprises'%20saw%204%25%20to%205%25%20rallies%2C%20or%20%2B180%20to%20225%20points.%20Thus%2C%20our%20100%20points%20rally%20tactical%20call%20might%20be%20on%20the%20low%20side%2C%26quot%3B%20Lee%20said%20in%20a%20Wednesday%20note%20to%20clients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20a%20positive%20reaction%20to%20lower%20inflation%20readings%20is%20driven%20by%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20emboldens%20the%20view%20of%20a%20soft%20landing%20scenario%20in%20the%20economy%2C%20in%20which%20a%20recession%20is%20ultimately%20avoided%20despite%20the%20aggressive%20monetary%20tightening%20from%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20over%20the%20past%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20low%20inflation%20reading%20also%20gives%20the%20Fed%20more%20breathing%20room%20in%20its%20interest%20rate%20decisions%2C%20with%20markets%20currently%20pricing%20in%20only%20one%20more%20interest%20rate%20hike%20for%20the%20year.%20Before%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-is-inflation-looking-consumer-price-index-june-data-2023-7%5C%22%3ECPI%20report%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20futures%20market%20had%20suggested%20the%20Fed%20might%20hike%20rates%20two%20more%20times%20before%20year-end.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20low%20inflation%20is%20great%20for%20consumers%20because%20wage%20growth%20is%20finally%20starting%20to%20outpace%20the%20rate%20of%20rising%20prices%2C%20which%20results%20in%20real%20income%20growth%20for%20consumers%20and%20gives%20them%20more%20spending%20power%2C%20which%20drives%20the%20bulk%20of%20the%20US%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELee%20expects%20June's%20low%20inflation%20reading%20to%20continue%20throughout%20the%20summer%2C%20which%20again%20could%20