s%20gorgeous%20but%20the%20insects%20carry%20guns%20and%20smoke%20cigars%2C%20never%20going%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20user%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYeah%2C%20Nah%2C%20just%20another%20reason%20to%20never%20go%20to%20Australia%2C%26quot%3B%20another%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BToo%20many%20spicy%20scorpions%2C%20fan%2C%20pencil%20things%20like%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20people%20from%20Australia%20said%20that%20they%20hope%20that%20the%20creepy%20crawly%20remains%20in%20the%20remote%20part%20of%20Western%20Australia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSaw%20one%20of%20these%20in%20Woodford%2C%20Queensland%2C%20a%20few%20days%20ago%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20recalled.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20definitely%20not%20something%20I%20wanted%20in%20my%20house!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENews.com.au%3C%2Fem%3E%20spoke%20to%20a%20Perth-based%20entomologist%20to%20identify%20the%20insect.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20walking%20stick%20insect%2C%20in%20the%20family%20Phasmatidae%2C%26quot%3B%20Nikolai%20Tatarnic%2C%20Curator%20of%20Entomology%20at%20the%20Western%20Australian%20Museum%20told%20the%20media%20outlet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20most%20people%20are%20aware%20of%20their%20camouflage%20(i.e.%20looking%20like%20a%20stick)%2C%20some%20species%20also%20engage%20in%20threat%20or%20startle%20displays%20(also%20called%20'deimatic%20behaviour')%20to%20ward%20off%20potential%20predators.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20think%20the%20insect%20in%20the%20clip%20is%20the%20genus%20Paronchestus%2C%20probably%20P.%20cornutus%2C%20as%20it%20closely%20resembles%20a%20specimen%20in%20our%20collection%2C%20which%20was%20collected%20from%20Laverton.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPhasmids%20are%20herbivores%20and%20are%20not%20venomous.%20The%20terrifying%20display%20in%20the%20video%20is%20all%20a%20ruse%2C%20but%20it%20clearly%20works.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPhasmids%20are%20found%20all%20across%20