ation%20Commissions%20do%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETruth%20commissions%20are%20independent%20or%20government%20groups%20that%20investigate%20political%20crimes%20and%20human%20rights%20violations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20early%201970s%2C%20several%20countries%20had%20adopted%20the%20Truth%20Commission%20%E2%80%93%20also%20called%20the%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commission%20or%20the%20Truth%20and%20Memory%20Commission%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%20to%20help%20the%20country%20acknowledge%20its%20conflict-ridden%20past%20and%20human%20rights%20violations%20that%20marked%20that%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20Commissions%20are%20usually%20associated%20with%20transitional%20justice%2C%20which%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ohchr.org%2Fen%2Ftransitional-justice%2Fabout-transitional-justice-and-human-rights%5C%22%3Ethe%20United%20Nations%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20comprises%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20full%20range%20of%20processes%20and%20mechanisms%20associated%20with%20a%20society%E2%80%99s%20attempt%20to%20come%20to%20terms%20with%20a%20legacy%20of%20large-scale%20past%20violations%20and%20abuses%20to%20ensure%20accountability%2C%20serve%20justice%2C%20and%20achieve%20reconciliation%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESouth%20America%20and%20Africa%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20have%20adopted%20such%20truth%20commissions.%20Canada%20set%20up%20one%20in%202008%20to%20investigate%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fnews.bbc.co.uk%2F2%2Fhi%2Famericas%2F7438079.stm%5C%22%3Eviolations%20in%20the%20First%20Nation%20Indian%20residential%20school%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%20(similar%20to%20the%20American-Indian%20boarding%20school%20systems%2C%20which%20involved%20the%20children%20of%20First%20Nation%20tribes%20being%20forcibly%20sent%20to%20residential%20schools%2C%20which%20were%20characterised%20by%20extreme%20discipline%20and%20often%20led%20to%20widespread%20abuse%20of%20the%20children%20as%20well%20as%20several%20deaths).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20latter%20was%20aimed%20at%20restorative%20rather%20than%20transitional%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fcanada-former-indigenous-schools-unmarked-graves%5C%22%3ECanada%E2%80%99s%20Long%20Overdue%20Reckoning%20With%20Its%20Colonial%20Past%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20the%20International%20Center%20for%20Transitional%20Justice%20released%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ictj.org%2Fresource-library%2Ftruth-reconciliation-and-redress-racial-injustice-united-states-insights%5C%22%3Ereport%20advocating%20a%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commission%20for%20the%20US%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20has%20%E2%80%9Cnever%20collectively%20confronted%20its%20history%20of%20colonialism%2C%20slavery%20and%20racism%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20reform%20the%20systems%20that%20perpetuate%20harms%20to%20Black%20communities%20and%20other%20marginalised%20and%20oppressed%20groups%2C%20or%20to%20redress%20these%20wrongs.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20suggested%20that%20while%20the%20US%20is%20not%20in%20a%20moment%20of%20transition%20%E2%80%9Cfrom%20armed%20conflict%20or%20authoritarian%20rule%20as%20may%20be%20the%20case%20for%20many%20countries%20that%20have%20undertaken%20a%20transitional%20justice%20process%2C%20it%20can%20learn%20from%20the%20experiences%20of%20these%20countries%20to%20confront%20its%20legacy%20of%20human%20rights%20violations.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commissions%20have%20also%20recognised%20the%20concept%20of%20learning%20from%20the%20past%2C%20as%20revealed%20by%20the%20processes%20of%20the%20Commission%2C%20so%20that%20the%20atrocities%20of%20the%20past%20and%20the%20systems%20that%20enabled%20those%20to%20take%20place%20do%20not%20repeat%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20evident%20from%20various%20reports%20such%20as%20the%20one%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Famerica.aljazeera.com%2Fopinions%2F2014%2F1%2Fargentina-conadeptruthcommissionhumanrights.html%5C%22%3EArgentina%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%201985%2C%20which%20was%20titled%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.desaparecidos.org%2Fnuncamas%2Fweb%2Fenglish%2Flibrary%2Fnevagain%2Fnevagain_001.htm%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ENunca%20M%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%C3%A1s%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3C%2Fa%3E(%E2%80%98Never%20Again%E2%80%99).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commission%20helps%20other%20countries%20and%20people%20groups%20to%20learn%20from%20it.%20These%20nations%20can%20look%20at%20these%20reports%20and%20see%20how%20exactly%20large-scale%20human%20rights%20violations%20were%20enabled%2C%20and%20can%20thus%20recognise%20symptoms%20and%20features%20in%20their%20own%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20common%20factors%20across%20these%20Commissions%20are%20that%20they%20are%20modes%20of%20dealing%20with%20the%3Cem%3E%20past%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20specifically%20a%20past%20that%20features%20various%20kinds%20of%20human%20rights%20violations%20and%20is%20not%20focused%20on%20a%20single%20event.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Commissions%20are%20also%20time-bound%20exercises%2C%20vested%20with%20the%20authority%20to%20investigate%20and%20seek%20information%20from%20victims%20of%20human%20rights%20abuse.%20They%20are%20expected%20to%20submit%20a%20report%20at%20the%20end%20of%20their%20term%2C%20as%20defined%20by%20Priscilla%20B.%20Hayner%20in%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F762562%5C%22%3Eearly%20comparative%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%2015%20Truth%20Commissions%20in%201994.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20with%20such%20a%20limited%20definition%20of%20the%20Truth%20Commission%2C%20it%20is%20possible%20to%20see%20its%20relevance%20for%20India%20and%20Indian%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20does%20India%20need%20a%20Truth%20Commission%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWomen%E2%80%99s%20groups%20in%20the%20Northeast%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwomens-groups-from-across-northeast-appeal-for-peace-in-manipur%5C%22%3Eclear%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20a%20Commission%20was%20necessary%20to%20%E2%80%9Cbegin%20processes%20of%20truth%20telling%2C%20healing%20and%20reconciliation%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20as%20mentioned%20earlier%2C%20they%20called%20for%20the%20establishment%20of%20a%20Northeast%20India%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20India%20is%20to%20set%20up%20a%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commission%2C%20should%20it%20only%20limit%20it%20to%20the%20Northeast%3F%20If%20we%20are%20to%20set%20its%20mandate%20in%20the%20past%2C%20which%20past%20are%20we%20considering%20as%20apt%20for%20such%20a%20Commission%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20about%20the%20human%20rights%20abuses%20during%20the%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fdefaultinterstitial.cms%5C%22%3E%20Emergency%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hrw.org%2Fnews%2F2014%2F10%2F29%2Findia-no-justice-1984-anti-sikh-bloodshed%5C%22%3Ethe%20Sikh%20riots%20of%201984%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newyorker.com%2Fmagazine%2F2015%2F06%2F29%2Fthe-great-divide-books-dalrymple%5C%22%3EPartition%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fvideo-gujarat-2002-northeast-delhi-2020-riots%5C%22%3E2002%20Gujarat%20riots%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%20And%20what%20about%20Kashmir%20and%20its%20long%20and%20terrible%20history%3B%20the%20atrocities%20on%20Dalits%2C%20such%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Findia-collective-conscience-justice-caste%5C%22%3EKhairlanji%20killings%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia%2Facquitted-in-tsundur-dalit-massacre-case-of-1991-get-busy-campaigning%2Fstory-wd8M0MkT2pQ0YXXZ4A49uM.html%5C%22%3ETsundur%20massacre%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20what%20about%20the%20Northeast%20with%20its%20history%20of%20unrest%20and%20the%20imposition%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fafspa-nagaland-civilian-killings%5C%22%3EArmed%20Forces%20(Special%20Powers)%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%20We%20also%20need%20to%20look%20at%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3Ecommunal%20riots%20that%20were%20an%20annual%20feature%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia%2Fhyderabad-ap-december-8-1990-over-200-dead%2Fstory-sN3L97xlBwVdIQDqkypWiI.html%5C%22%3EHyderabad%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%201980s%20and%20early%201990s%3F%20And%20we%20need%20to%20consider%20the%20systematic%20oppression%20and%20marginalisation%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fnarendra-modi-dilemma-minority-outreach-hindutva-backlash%5C%22%3Eminorities%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20past%20ten%20years%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fafspa-nagaland-civilian-killings%5C%22%3EAFSPA%2C%20the%20Law%20That%20Allows%20Incidents%20Like%20the%20Nagaland%20Killings%20to%20Occur%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhich%20of%20these%20issues%20will%20a%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commission%20address%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20we%20are%20to%20set%20up%20a%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commission%2C%20we%20need%20to%20ask%20ourselves%20what%20we%20hope%20to%20achieve%20by%20doing%20so.%20To%20return%20to%20Hayner%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20most%20straightforward%20reason%20to%20set%20up%20a%20truth%20commission%20is%20that%20of%20sanctioned%20fact-finding%3A%20establish%20an%20accurate%20record%20of%20a%20country%E2%80%99s%20past%2C%20and%20thus%20help%20to%20provide%20a%20fair%20record%20of%20a%20country%E2%80%99s%20history%20and%20its%20government%E2%80%99s%20much-disputed%20acts.%20Leaving%20an%20honest%20account%20of%20the%20violence%20prevents%20history%20from%20being%20lost%20or%20re-written%2C%20and%20allows%20a%20society%20to%20learn%20from%20its%20past%20in%20order%20to%20prevent%20a%20repetition%20of%20such%20violence%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20presupposes%20that%20we%20as%20a%20nation%20believe%20that%20it%20is%20necessary%20to%20face%20up%20to%20what%20happened%20in%20the%20past%20and%20to%20record%20it%2C%20that%20we%20believe%20that%20this%20history%20%3Cem%3Eteaches%20%3C%2Fem%3Eus%2C%20even%20if%20it%20is%20unpleasant%20and%20disturbing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIs%20it%20possible%20for%20us%20to%20think%20the%20unthinkable%3A%20that%20we%20in%20India%20are%20condemned%20to%20repeat%20these%20cycles%20of%20human%20rights%20violations%20and%20extreme%20violence%20because%20we%20have%20not%2C%20at%20any%20point%2C%20in%20our%2076%20years%20of%20independence%2C%20confronted%20and%20dealt%20with%20the%20sequences%20of%20violence%20that%20have%20periodically%20erupted%20in%20our%20land%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20wounds%20of%20the%20Partition%20were%20papered%20over%20by%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20fasts%20and%20appeals%2C%20the%20following%20episodes%2C%20whether%20of%20communal%20or%20caste%20violence%2C%20were%20left%20unaddressed%2C%20except%20for%20token%20apologies%20and%20minimal%20compensation%20to%20the%20victims%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20were%20never%20identified.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20had%20set%20up%20commissions%20to%20investigate%20some%20of%20these%20human%20rights%20violations.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcountercurrents.org%2Fcc280615.htm%5C%22%3EShah%20Commission%20of%20Enquiry%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20set%20up%20to%20account%20for%20the%20excesses%20of%20the%20Emergency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20we%20have%20not%20set%20up%20a%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commission%2C%20nor%20have%20we%20attempted%20to%20learn%20from%20those%20such%20as%20the%20South%20African%20or%20Rwandan%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commissions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F12125355%2F614643006_3a3b122402_b.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22740%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F12125355%2F614643006_3a3b122402_b.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F12125355%2F614643006_3a3b122402_b-300x225.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-662786%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22555%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERwanda%20formed%20a%20National%20Unity%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commission%20in%201999%20after%20the%20brutal%20Rwandan%20genocide%2C%20in%20which%20more%20than%20a%20million%20Rwandans%20died%20and%20two%20million%20were%20displaced.%20Photo%3A%20Flickr%2FRobin%20Kirk.%20CC%20BY-2.0.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20demand%20for%20the%20setting%20up%20of%20a%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commission%20also%20presupposes%20that%20the%20nation%20is%20acknowledging%20wrongdoing%2C%20of%20violence%20perpetrated%2C%20of%20the%20abuse%20of%20trust%20and%20a%20shared%20culpability.%20The%20women%E2%80%99s%20groups%20in%20the%20Northeast%20were%20clear%20in%20that%20they%20were%20looking%20to%20%E2%80%9Cshare%20the%20many%20challenges%2C%20tell%20our%20stories%2C%20acknowledge%20the%20mistakes%20and%20work%20toward%20collective%20healing%20and%20forgiveness%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20their%20statement%2C%20the%20women%20groups%20outlined%20the%20process%20and%20purpose%20of%20the%20Commission%3A%20that%20they%20work%20towards%20sharing%20truths%20and%20stories%2C%20that%20there%20is%20honesty%20and%20through%20that%20process%20there%20can%20eventually%20be%20healing%20and%20forgiveness.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20the%20hope%20for%20healing%20that%20the%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commissions%20engender%20is%20one%20that%20is%20open%20to%20question.%20This%20is%20because%20there%20are%20several%20accounts%20of%20how%20victims%20are%20re-traumatised%20by%20having%20to%20narrate%20the%20violence%20they%20suffered.%20Moreover%2C%20there%20is%20limited%20time%20to%20spend%20on%20each%20person%E2%80%99s%20testimony%20and%20there%20is%20no%20follow-up%20support%20or%20help%20afterwards.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20challenges%20and%20issues%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commissions%20are%20set%20up%20when%20a%20transition%20is%20underway%20or%20has%20just%20taken%20place%2C%20or%20when%20a%20newly%20installed%20government%20seeks%20to%20acknowledge%20the%20past%20and%20look%20to%20a%20better%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20that%20context%2C%20how%20would%20it%20work%20for%20India%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20history%20of%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commissions%20shows%20that%20they%20have%20been%20set%20up%20mainly%20during%20a%20transition%20or%20when%20a%20government%20faces%20international%20pressure%20regarding%20its%20human%20rights%20record%20and%20hopes%20to%20manipulate%20public%20opinion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20latter%20context%2C%20a%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commission%20may%20not%20be%20a%20valid%20mechanism%20to%20help%20towards%20a%20new%20future.%20It%20could%20well%20be%20a%20manipulative%20political%20tool%20which%20is%20used%20to%20legitimise%20a%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20such%20a%20Commission%20set%20up%20in%20good%20faith%20and%20tasked%20with%20creating%20a%20timely%20report%20of%20the%20truth%20of%20human%20rights%20violations%20has%20been%20acknowledged%20as%20a%20mechanism%20that%20helps%20a%20society%20to%20move%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20difficult%20challenges%20for%20the%20establishment%20of%20a%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commission%20in%20India%20is%20with%20regard%20to%20the%20word%20%E2%80%98truth%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20vitiated%20nature%20of%20the%20meaning%20of%20%E2%80%98truth%E2%80%99%20in%20contemporary%20societies%2C%20such%20as%20those%20of%20the%20US%20and%20India%2C%20with%20people%20believing%20in%20alternative%20truths%20and%20emotional%20truths%2C%20is%20it%20possible%20to%20think%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98truth%E2%80%99%20as%20stable%20and%20factual%20anymore%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthe-contours-of-indias-post-truth-state%5C%22%3EThe%20Contours%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20Post-Truth%20State%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETruth%20Commissions%20rely%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Fit-rules-single-source-of-truth-governance%5C%22%3Efact-finding%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20truth-telling%2C%20but%20in%20this%20era%20of%20relative%20truths%2C%20where%20people%20compete%20for%20their%20truths%20to%20be%20acknowledged%20as%20the%20only%20truth%2C%20what%20chance%20does%20a%20Commission%20stand%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20challenge%20to%20establishing%20a%20Truth%20Commission%20in%20India%20is%20with%20regard%20to%20who%20will%20actually%20institute%20one.%20While%20civil%20society%20might%20believe%20itself%20to%20be%20essential%20to%20this%20process%2C%20these%20Commissions%20have%20worked%20best%20when%20they%20are%20established%20by%20a%20country%E2%80%99s%20executive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hrw.org%2Fnews%2F2014%2F10%2F29%2Findia-no-justice-1984-anti-sikh-bloodshed%5C%22%3ECommissions%20set%20up%20by%20civil%20society%3C%2Fa%3E%20rarely%20have%20the%20same%20validity%20and%20endorsement%2C%20and%20their%20reports%20do%20not%20carry%20the%20same%20heft.%20But%20if%20a%20Commission%20is%20set%20up%20by%20the%20State%2C%20then%20its%20findings%20are%20usually%20watered%20down%20%E2%80%93%20especially%20where%20the%20human%20rights%20violations%20are%20in%20line%20with%20the%20ideology%20of%20the%20State%20%E2%80%93%20and%20will%20avoid%20acknowledging%20unpalatable%20truths%20through%20acts%20of%20omission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20there%20remains%20the%20elephant%20in%20this%20particular%20room%3A%20why%20will%20a%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commission%20be%20set%20up%20when%20several%20of%20those%20who%20have%20been%20or%20are%20in%20power%20might%20fear%20that%20they%20will%20be%20implicated%20in%20the%20findings%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20this%20remains%20true%20irrespective%20of%20which%20party%20is%20in%20power%20at%20any%20given%20time%3A%20people%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthefederal.com%2Fnews%2F1984-anti-sikh-riots-justice-delayed-and-denied-convictions-few-and-far-between%2F%5C%22%3Estill%20awaiting%20justice%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%201984%20anti-Sikh%20riots%2C%20and%20all%20the%20commissions%20set%20up%20to%20investigate%20the%20riots%20have%20been%20inconclusive%20in%20their%20findings%20as%20to%20who%20can%20be%20named%20as%20the%20perpetrator.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20the%20leaders%20of%20several%2C%20if%20not%20all%20the%20political%20parties%20in%20India%2C%20are%20indirectly%20or%20directly%20responsible%20for%20many%20of%20the%20human%20rights%20violations%20in%20the%20country%20is%20a%20%E2%80%98given%E2%80%99%2C%20known%20to%20many.%20However%2C%20there%20is%20little%20stomach%20for%20an%20open%20acknowledgement%20of%20this%20fact%20and%20hence%20for%20a%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20because%20a%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commission%20has%2C%20as%20one%20of%20its%20main%20features%2C%20the%20open%20acknowledgement%20of%20the%20truths%20of%20abuse%20and%20how%20its%20perpetration%20was%20made%20possible%20by%20the%20institutions%20of%20the%20state%20and%20its%20leaders.%20Even%20though%20there%20is%20no%20authority%20for%20a%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commission%20to%20recommend%20prosecution%20or%20the%20meting%20out%20of%20justice%2C%20the%20very%20acknowledgement%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98truth%E2%80%99%20is%20often%20seen%20as%20a%20deterrent%20enough%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F44218484%5C%22%3EWriting%20about%20the%20limitations%20of%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commissions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Eric%20Brahm%20speaks%20of%20how%2C%20for%20many%2C%20they%20%E2%80%9Crepresent%20some%20form%20of%20accountability%20for%20human%20rights%20abuses%20when%20historically%20this%20has%20been%20rare%20the%20world%20over%E2%80%9D.%20This%20is%20considered%20a%20virtue%20when%20the%20only%20other%20option%20is%20that%20there%20is%20no%20accountability%20whatsoever%2C%20victims%20are%20ignored%2C%20their%20stories%20untold%20and%20there%20is%20little%20possibility%20of%20reconciliation%2C%20renewal%2C%20and%20peaceful%20coexistence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20viewpoint%20is%20the%20one%20that%20claims%20that%20the%20prosecution%20of%20criminals%20is%20far%20more%20effective%20than%20the%20Commision%E2%80%99s%20discovery%20of%20underlying%20patterns%20and%20institutions%20which%20facilitated%20the%20large-scale%20violence%20and%20abuse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20generally%2C%20this%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20happen%2C%20as%20the%20prosecutions%20are%20usually%20weak-willed%20and%20ineffective%20and%20the%20truth%20is%20shrouded%20in%20secrecy.%20The%20acknowledgement%20of%20abuse%20is%20as%20rare%20as%20the%20prosecution%20of%20perpetrators.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20patterns%20which%20led%20to%20human%20rights%20violations%20might%20be%20discernible%20to%20even%20the%20general%20public%2C%20there%20is%20no%20acknowledgment%20of%20them%2C%20and%20consequently%2C%20no%20accountability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20usual%20options%20after%20a%20sequence%20of%20human%20rights%20violations%20are%20juridical%20intervention%20and%20punitive%20action%20for%20perpetrators%20versus%20a%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commission%2C%20which%20may%20not%20lead%20to%20punishment%20for%20the%20guilty%20but%20will%20provide%20a%20space%20wherein%20the%20truth%20%3Cem%3Ecan%20be%20told%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20ideally%20both%20should%20be%20possible%2C%20that%20is%20rarely%20so.%20Punitive%20action%20is%20usually%20only%20for%20whom%20Brahm%20calls%20the%20%E2%80%9Clowest%20level%20perpetrators%E2%80%9D%20rather%20than%20for%20the%20leadership.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20context%2C%20a%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commission%2C%20which%20makes%20it%20possible%20to%20identify%20the%20system%20that%20enabled%20the%20human%20rights%20abuse%20and%20those%20who%20set%20up%20the%20system%20or%20benefitted%20from%20it%2C%20seems%20a%20better%20alternative%20insofar%20as%20people%20will%20at%20least%20know%20the%20route%20that%20was%20taken%20to%20get%20to%20this%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20while%20the%20highest%20level%20of%20perpetrators%20may%20never%20be%20held%20accountable%2C%20to%20be%20known%20and%20named%20in%20a%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commission%20report%20is%20itself%20a%20move%20forward%20from%20absolutely%20no%20accountability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20when%20the%20women%20of%20the%20Northeast%20asked%20for%20a%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commission%20%2C%20just%20when%20the%20violence%20in%20Manipur%20began%2C%20it%20was%20a%20radical%20departure%20from%20the%20norm%2C%20demonstrating%20a%20willingness%20to%20confront%20the%20truth%2C%20to%20acknowledge%20one%E2%80%99s%20own%20culpability%20and%2For%20victimhood%2C%20a%20determination%20to%20try%20to%20move%20on%20into%20a%20new%2C%20better%20future%20marked%20by%20some%20degree%20of%20healing%20and%20reconciliation%2C%20and%20a%20greater%20commitment%20to%20human%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20their%20request%20has%20disappeared%20in%20the%20light%20of%20the%20fires%20burning%20in%20Manipur.%20We%20prefer%20to%20watch%20the%20fires%20burn%20than%20to%20ask%20for%20accountability%20and%20the%20acknowledgement%20of%20our%20own%20failures%20or%20culpability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20will%20India%20ever%20set%20up%20a%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commission%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fanna-kurian%5C%22%3EAnna%20Kurian%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0teaches%20at%20the%20department%20of%20English%20in%20the%20University%20of%20Hyderabad.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689159649000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F04223216%2Fimage-968.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Ftruth-and-reconciliation-in-india%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22If%20India%20is%20to%20set%20up%20a%20Truth%20and%20Reconciliation%20Commission%2C%20should%20it%20only%20limit%20it%20to%20the%20Northeast%3F%20If%20we%20are%20to%20set%20its%20mandate%20in%20the%20past%2C%20which%20past%20are%20we%20considering%20as%20apt%20for%20such%20a%20Commission%3F%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Ftruth-and-reconciliation-in-india%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Rise%20of%20Rishi%20Sunak%2C%20Other%20Young%20Leaders%20Show%20West%20Puts%20a%20Political%20Premium%20on%20Youth%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F12152144%2FUntitled-design-2023-07-12T152108.363.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3ELondon%20Calling%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0How%20does%20India%20look%20from%20afar%3F%20Looming%20world%20power%20or%20dysfunctional%20democracy%3F%20And%20what%E2%80%99s%20happening%20in%20Britain%2C%20and%20the%20West%2C%20that%20India%20needs%20to%20know%20about%20and%20perhaps%20learn%20from%3F%20This%20fortnightly%20column%20helps%20forge%20the%20connections%20so%20essential%20in%20our%20globalising%20world.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYou%20would%20have%20to%20be%20colour%20blind%20not%20to%20notice%20the%20remarkable%20rise%20of%20politicians%20of%20South%20Asian%20heritage%20to%20the%20very%20top%20of%20British%20politics.%20Yes%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20Rishi%20Sunak%20%E2%80%93%20the%20UK%E2%80%99s%20first%20desi%20PM.%20But%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20just%20him.%20Not%20at%20all!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%E2%80%99s%20the%20First%20Minister%20of%20Scotland%20(Humza%20Yousaf)%2C%20the%20Mayor%20of%20London%20(Sadiq%20Khan)%2C%20the%20British%20Home%20Secretary%20(Suella%20Braverman)%2C%20and%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20Scottish%20Labour%20Party%20(Anas%20Sarwar).%20The%20trend%20even%20extends%20to%20the%20only%20country%20with%20which%20the%20UK%20shares%20a%20land%20border%20%E2%80%93%20Leo%20Varadkar%20is%20the%20Taoiseach%20or%20Prime%20Minister%20of%20the%20Irish%20Republic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20communities%20which%2C%20a%20generation%20ago%2C%20were%20politically%20almost%20invisible%20at%20the%20national%20level%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20startling%20change.%20And%20all%20the%20more%20so%20because%20these%20leaders%20have%20got%20to%20the%20top%20while%20still%20young.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESunak%20became%20Britain%E2%80%99s%20youngest%20prime%20minister%20for%20well%20over%20200%20years%20when%20he%20took%20office%20last%20October%20at%20the%20age%20of%2042%3B%20Yousaf%20rose%20to%20the%20top%20in%20Scotland%20earlier%20this%20year%20aged%2038%2C%20the%20youngest%20First%20Minister%20since%20Scotland%E2%80%99s%20devolved%20government%20was%20established%20in%201999.%20Khan%20was%20first%20elected%20Mayor%20of%20London%20at%2045%3B%20Braverman%20was%20appointed%20to%20lead%20the%20Home%20Office%2C%20regarded%20by%20many%20as%20London%E2%80%99s%20toughest%20political%20post%2C%20at%2042%3B%20Varadkar%20reached%20the%20summit%20of%20Irish%20politics%20at%2038%3B%20Sarwar%20became%20party%20leader%20in%20Scotland%20at%2037.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20exception%20of%20Anas%20Sarwar%20%E2%80%93%20whose%20father%20was%20a%20British%20MP%20who%20went%20on%20to%20serve%20as%20the%20Governor%20of%20Punjab%20province%20in%20Pakistan%20%E2%80%93%20none%20of%20these%20are%20from%20political%20dynasties.%20They%20made%20it%20on%20their%20own%20through%20ambition%2C%20talent%20and%20%E2%80%93%20as%20always%20%E2%80%93%20a%20fair%20measure%20of%20good%20fortune.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20part%20of%20a%20bigger%20trend%20in%20British%20politics.%20The%20time%20when%20veteran%20politicians%2C%20wise%20old%20heads%2C%20had%20a%20monopoly%20on%20the%20top%20jobs%20is%20long%20over.%20Winston%20Churchill%20was%2080%20when%20he%20finally%20packed%20it%20in%20as%20PM%20back%20in%201955.%20Since%20then%2C%20Britain%20has%20never%20had%20a%20prime%20minister%20in%20their%2070s.%20And%20you%20have%20to%20stretch%20back%20almost%20half%20a%20century%20to%20the%20last%20time%20a%20British%20PM%20was%2060%20or%20above%20when%20he%20or%20she%20first%20took%20office.%20Tony%20Blair%20and%20David%20Cameron%20were%20both%20in%20their%20early%2040s%20when%20they%20first%20entered%2010%20Downing%20Street%20and%20Boris%20Johnson%20was%20distinctly%20on%20the%20old%20side%20when%20he%20took%20over%20as%20PM%20at%2055.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20generational%20shift%20is%20evident%20in%20many%20leading%20Western%20democracies.%20Emanuel%20Macron%20was%2039%20when%20he%20first%20was%20elected%20as%20France%E2%80%99s%20President%3B%20Mette%20Frederiksen%20was%2041%20when%20she%20became%20the%20Danish%20PM%20%E2%80%93%20the%20same%20age%20at%20which%20Volodymyr%20Zelensky%20became%20Ukraine%E2%80%99s%20President%3B%20Justin%20Trudeau%20became%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20leader%20at%2043%3B%20Giorgia%20Meloni%20recently%20came%20to%20the%20helm%20in%20Italy%20at%2045%2C%20and%20Pedro%20Sanchez%20was%20a%20year%20older%20when%20he%20became%20Spain%E2%80%99s%20head%20of%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20of%20course%20exceptions.%20Olaf%20Scholz%20took%20power%20as%20Germany%E2%80%99s%20Chancellor%20at%20the%20seasoned%20age%20of%2063%3B%20and%20Keir%20Starmer%2C%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20British%20Labour%20Party%2C%20is%20odds%20on%20favourite%20to%20win%20the%20next%20UK%20election%2C%20by%20which%20time%20he%20will%20be%20a%20whiskery%2061%20or%2062.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYounger%20politicians%20don%E2%80%99t%20necessarily%20bring%20better%20governance%2C%20but%20they%20do%20suggest%20that%20political%20deference%20towards%20time-serving%20veterans%20%E2%80%93%20leaders%20who%20are%20sometimes%20low%20on%20energy%20and%20not%20exactly%20up-to-speed%20on%20the%20public%20mood%20%E2%80%93%20is%20fading%20away.%20Increasingly%2C%20the%20political%20centre%20of%20gravity%20is%20settling%20nearer%20to%20a%20nation%E2%80%99s%20median%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20also%20a%20sharp%20break%20from%20political%20business-as-usual.%20Older%20politicians%20are%20seen%20as%20mired%20in%20the%20failed%20policies%20which%20produced%20the%202008%20financial%20crisis%2C%20the%20baleful%20effects%20of%20which%20still%20haunt%20us%2C%20and%20complacent%20in%20the%20face%20of%20the%20climate%20crisis%20and%20increasing%20social%20inequality.%20Some%20of%20the%20most%20high-profile%20of%20the%20new%20generation%20of%20leaders%20%E2%80%93%20Jacinda%20Ardern%20in%20New%20Zealand%20and%20Sanna%20Marin%20in%20Finland%2C%20for%20example%20%E2%80%93%20have%20moved%20on%2C%20but%20the%20appetite%20for%20new%20ideas%20and%20new%20faces%20endures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20emphasis%20on%20youth%20has%20not%20spread%20much%20beyond%20the%20West.%20For%20most%20of%20the%20past%2030%20years%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20prime%20ministers%20have%20been%20in%20their%2070s%20%E2%80%93%20and%20you%20have%20to%20go%20back%20to%20V.P.%20Singh%20to%20come%20across%20a%20politician%20who%20made%20it%20to%20the%20top%20job%20before%20he%20was%2060.%20President%20Cyril%20Ramaphosa%20of%20South%20Africa%20is%2070%3B%20Lula%2C%20Brazil%E2%80%99s%20le