t%20on%20July%2011%20asked%20the%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Board%20of%20India%20(SEBI)%20to%20explain%20why%20the%20law%20was%20tweaked%20in%202018%20that%20allegedly%20limited%20the%20markets%20regulator%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20investigate%20opacity%20in%20the%20ownership%20structure%20of%20foreign%20portfolio%20investors%20(FPIs).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20March%202%2C%20the%20top%20court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fsupreme-court-forms-expert-panel-to-probe-any-regulatory-failure-on-adani-issue%2Farticle66570758.ece%5C%22%3Ehad%20passed%3C%2Fa%3E%20an%20order%20to%20set%20up%20a%20five-member%20expert%20committee%20to%20investigate%20the%20allegations%20made%20by%20Hindenburg%20Research%20against%20Adani%20Group.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20expert%20committee%2C%20headed%20by%20former%20Supreme%20Court%20judge%20A.M.%20Sapre%2C%20had%20said%20that%20the%20provisions%20of%20requiring%20FPI%20to%20disclose%20%E2%80%9Cultimate%20natural%20person%E2%80%9D%20were%20done%20away%20with%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20this%20led%20to%20SEBI%20hitting%20a%20wall%20in%20its%20investigation%20on%20the%20Hindenburg-Adani%20case%2C%20the%20expert%20committee%20report%20had%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fsupreme-court-asks-sebi-why-law-was-tweaked-to-remove-provisions-prohibiting-opacity-in-fpi-ownership%2Farticle67067397.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20advocate%20Prashant%20Bhushan%2C%20on%20the%20petitioners%E2%80%99%20side%2C%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9CSEBI%E2%80%99s%20change%20of%20its%20FPI%20law%20in%202018%20is%20absolutely%20fatal%20to%20its%20current%20investigation.%20They%20have%20removed%20the%20very%20definition%20of%20%E2%80%98opaque%20structure%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20FPI%20Regulations%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSEBI%20cannot%20do%20anything%20now%20in%20its%20present%20investigation.%20The%20amendments%20to%20provisions%20concerning%20opaque%20structure%20of%20FPIs%2C%20its%20beneficial%20owners%20and%20related%20party%20transactions%20were%20made%20to%20prevent%20such%20frauds%20from%20being%20exposed%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fbecause-of-repealed-provisions-sebi-hit-opaque-structure-wall-while-investigating-adani-sc-panel%5C%22%3EBecause%20of%20Repealed%20Provisions%2C%20SEBI%20Hit%20%E2%80%98Opaque%20Structure%E2%80%99%20Wall%20While%20Investigating%20Adani%3A%20SC%20Panel%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChief%20Justice%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%2C%20therefore%2C%20asked%20Solicitor%20General%20Tushar%20Mehta%2C%20appearing%20for%20SEBI%3A%20%E2%80%9CMr.%20Solicitor%2C%20we%20certainly%20would%20like%20to%20know%20why%20you%20%5BSEBI%5D%20made%20these%20changes.%20Apropos%20what%20Mr.%20Bhushan%20said%2C%20SEBI%20may%20be%20prevented%20from%20going%20into%20the%20layers%20of%20transactions%20because%20of%20these%20amendments.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECJI%20Chandrachud%20asked%20%E2%80%98what%20are%20the%20circumstances%20under%20which%20you%20had%20changed%20the%20provisions%20dealing%20with%20%E2%80%98opaque%20structure%E2%80%99%E2%80%A6%20%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESolicitor%20General%20Mehta%20responded%20saying%20that%20the%20SEBI%20investigation%20%E2%80%9Cis%20going%20on%20at%20full%20speed%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20newspaper%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20given%20it%20time%20till%20August%2014%20to%20complete%20the%20investigation%20into%20the%20Adani%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAhead%20of%20the%20hearing%2C%20SEBI%20had%20defended%20the%20changes%20in%20the%20law%20saying%20the%20alteration%20did%20not%20make%20it%20tougher%20to%20identify%20the%20ultimate%20beneficiaries%20of%20offshore%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%2041-page%20affidavit%2C%20as%20reported%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businesstoday.in%2Flatest%2Fcorporate%2Fstory%2Fadani-hindenburg-case-sebi-files-41-page-affidavit-in-sc-hearing-on-tuesday-389006-2023-07-10%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Today%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20capital%20markets%20regulator%20said%20it%20did%20not%20agree%20with%20the%20expert%20committee%E2%80%99s%20observations%20of%20difficulties%20in%20identifying%20holders%20of%20economic%20interest%20behind%20an%20offshore%20fund.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20opposed%20the%20expert%20committee%E2%80%99s%20recommendation%20that%20the%20regulator%20must%20be%20given%20a%20firm%20timeline%20to%20complete%20its%20probe%20and%20that%20must%20be%20%E2%80%9Dembedded%20into%20the%20law%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESEBI%20said%20prescribing%20such%20limits%20%E2%80%9Dmay%20compromise%20the%20quality%20of%20investigation%E2%80%9D%2C%20create%20constraints%20and%20increase%20litigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20SEBI%20as%20saying%20that%20the%20difficulty%20to%20probe%20the%20allegations%20against%20Adani%20Group%20lay%20in%20the%20existence%20of%20thresholds%20for%20determination%20of%20beneficial%20owners%20of%20the%20FPIs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSince%20granular%20details%20of%20all%20underlying%20investors%20with%20ownership%2C%20economic%2C%20or%20control%20interest%20in%20entities%20below%20the%20threshold%20was%20never%20required%20to%20be%20made%20available%20to%20the%20Designated%20Depository%20Participants%2FCustodian%20of%20Securities%2C%20there%20was%20a%20possibility%20that%20the%20same%20natural%20person%20could%20hold%20a%20significant%20aggregate%20economic%20interest%20in%20the%20FPI%20via%20different%20investing%20entities%2C%20each%20of%20which%20were%20individually%20below%20the%20threshold%20for%20identification%20as%20a%20BO%20%5Bbeneficial%20owner%5D%2C%E2%80%9D%20SEBI%2C%20represented%20by%20advocate%20Pratap%20Venugopal%2C%20said%20in%20its%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read